claims:
Claims claimed is: 1 A method of forming a spacer layer, the method comprising: disposing a substrate in an internal volume of a processing chamber, the substrate having a film formed thereon, the film comprising silicon, carbon, nitrogen, and hydrogen; introducing a process gas into the processing chamber, wherein the process gas comprises high pressure steam; exposing the film to the process gas to form a reacted film, such that the reacted film comprises silicon, carbon, oxygen, and hydrogen; and purging the internal volume with an inert gas 2. The method of claim 1 , wherein the high pressure steam is at a pressure between about 2 bar and about 50 bar. 3. The method of claim 1 , wherein the film is formed by an atomic layer deposition (ALD) process. 4. The method of claim 1 , wherein the substrate is disposed on a substrate support and the substrate support is maintained at a temperate between about 200 degrees Celsius and about 500 degrees Celsius during exposing the film to the process gas 5. The method of claim 1 , further comprising treating the reacted film with a hydrogen anneal. 6. The method of claim 1 , wherein the substrate comprises a fin field effect transistor structure. 7. A method of forming a spacer layer, the method comprising: disposing a substrate in an internal volume of a processing chamber, the substrate having a film formed thereon, the film comprising silicon, carbon, nitrogen, and hydrogen; 

 introducing a process gas into the processing chamber, wherein the process gas comprises high pressure steam; exposing the film to the process gas to form a reacted film, such that the reacted film comprises silicon, carbon, oxygen, and hydrogen; purging the internal volume with an inert gas; and treating the reacted film with a hydrogen anneal. 8. The method of claim 7, wherein the high pressure steam is at a pressure between about 2 bar and about 50 bar. 9. The method of claim 7, wherein the process gas further comprises a carrier gas. 10. The method of claim 7, wherein the substrate comprises a fin field effect transistor structure 11. The method of claim 7, wherein the substrate is disposed on a substrate support, and the substrate support is maintained at a temperate between about 200 degrees Celsius and about 500 degrees Celsius during exposing the film to the process gas. 12. The method of claim 7, wherein the hydrogen anneal comprises exposing the reacted film to a hydrogen-containing gas, the hydrogen-containing gas comprising hydrogen gas. 13. A method of forming a spacer layer, the method comprising: disposing a substrate in an internal volume of a processing chamber, the substrate having a film formed thereon, the film comprising silicon, carbon, nitrogen, and hydrogen, the substrate comprising silicon and germanium; introducing a process gas into the processing chamber, wherein the process gas comprises high pressure steam; 

 exposing the film to the process gas to form a reacted film, such that the reacted film comprises silicon, carbon, oxygen, and hydrogen; purging the internal volume with an inert gas; and treating the reacted film with a hydrogen anneal. 14. The method of claim 13, wherein the substrate is disposed on a substrate support, and the substrate support is maintained at a temperate between about 200 degrees Celsius and about 500 degrees Celsius during exposing the film to the process gas. 15. The method of claim 13, wherein the substrate comprises a fin field effect transistor structure.
